      • doTransaction

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> doTransaction(int type,
                                                      java.lang.String... args)
                                               throws TransactionException
        Performs the requested transaction with the given string arguments.
        Parameters:
        transaction - Integer representing the type of transaction to be performed
        args - The arguments needed to perform the given transaction.
        Returns:
        Returns a list of strings as the "output" (if there is any).
        Throws:
        TransactionException - Thrown if the transaction cannot be performed. A message should be included explaining why the transaction failed.
